.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
File types will be deduced unless explicitly specfied with the
\fBinput\-format\fP and/or \fBoutput\-format\fP options.  For file
types like PIX that do not encode dimensional information, \fBicv\fP
will attempt to guess the image size based on various assumptions (a
square image, known sizes for image displays, paper sizes at various
dots\-per\-inch, etc.).  If the users does know the correct image width
and height, they may be specified with the \fBw\fP and \fBn\fP
options.
.sp
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP
.RS 4
Print help and exit.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-i\fP \fIfile\fP, \fB\-\-input\fP \fIfile\fP
.RS 4
Specify an input file.  If none is
specified, the first non\-option\-related argument will be used as the
input file name.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-o\fP \fIfile\fP, \fB\-\-output\fP \fIfile\fP
.RS 4
Specify an input file.  If none is
specified, the second non\-option\-related argument will be used as the
output file name.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-w\fP \fI\fP, \fB\-\-width\fP \fI\fP
.RS 4
Specify the width of the input image.
Useful for file types such as PIX that do not encode explicit size
information.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-n\fP \fI\fP, \fB\-\-height\fP \fI\fP
.RS 4
Specify the height of the input image.
Useful for file types such as PIX that do not encode explicit size
information.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-input\-format\fP \fIfmt\fP
.RS 4
Explicitly specify input file format.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-output\-format\fP \fIfmt\fP
.RS 4
Explicitly specify output file format.
.RE
